channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed

item.title: Kamala Harris Is Trying Out Campaign Slogans - and We Have Some Suggestions

item.title: NYT/Siena College Poll: Trump Leads Harris
item.description: Republican Donald Trump leads Democratic Vice President Kamala Harris by 48% to 46% in a New York Times/Siena College poll of registered voters conducted July 22 to 24 and published on Thursday.

item.title: Remembering Former Rep. Tommy Robinson
item.description: "No one - including Bill Clinton - has ever dominated the media in Arkansas like Tommy Robinson did in the 1980s," Rex Nelson, former newsman and longtime right-hand man to the state's former Republican Gov. Mike Huckabee, told Newsmax.

Arizona senate candidate says Mark Kelly would give Harris 'jolt' as VP
item.description: Arizona Democratic Senate candidate Rep. Ruben Gallego said Sen. Mark Kelly, D-Ariz., would provide a "jolt" to Vice President Kamala Harris' campaign as running mate.

item.title: Ryan: Schools in Jackson, Miss. Saddled with DEI Initiatives
item.description: If the people who run Jackson Public Schools cared as much about their students as they do promoting DEI, their students would see as much success and improvement as other students in the state.
